  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      -  There is evidence that inflammatory processes may play detrimental role during the acute
           phase of myocardial infarction

        -  The hypothesis of this study is that colchicine, by its anti-inflammatory action, may
           lead to reduction in infarct size, when administered during the acute phase of
           myocardial infarction
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
